[30;1m216 | [0m[35mwould be blocking (read or write on a socket), the file descriptor is added[0m
[30;1m217 | [0m[35mto an event loop managed by gevent, and the scheduler will switch tasks.[0m
[30;1m218 | [0m[35mSince gevent uses cooperative multi-tasking, a task that is CPU-bound will[0m
[30;1m219 | [0m[35mnot yield control to the gevent scheduler, limiting concurrency. For this[0m
[30;1m220 | [0m[35mreason, gevent is a good choice for tasks that perform lots of socket I/O,[0m
[30;1m221 | [0m[35mbut may give worse performance for tasks that are CPU-bound (e.g., parsing[0m
[30;1m222 | [0m[35mlarge files, manipulating images, generating reports, etc). Understand the[0m

[30;1m169 | [0m[35mRetrying tasks that fail[0m
[30;1m170 | [0m[35m------------------------[0m
[30;1m171 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m172 | [0m[35mSometimes we may have a task that we anticipate might fail from time to time,[0m
[30;1m173 | [0m[35min which case we should retry it. Huey supports automatically retrying tasks a[0m
[30;1m174 | [0m[35mgiven number of times, optionally with a delay between attempts.[0m
[30;1m175 | [0m[35m[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m609[0m[34m of [0m[33m902[0m[31m ]--[0m

[30;1m150 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m151 | [0m[35m* ``*`` - always true, e.g. if ``hour='*'``, then the rule matches any hour.[0m
[30;1m152 | [0m[35m* ``*/n`` - every *n* interval, e.g. ``minute='*/15'`` means every 15 minutes.[0m
[30;1m153 | [0m[35m* ``m-n`` - run every time ``m..n`` inclusive.[0m
[30;1m154 | [0m[35m* ``m,n`` - run on *m* and *n*.[0m
[30;1m155 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m156 | [0m[35mMultiple rules can be expressed by separating the individual rules with a[0m

[30;1m440 | [0m[35m            executed at intervals in isolation, they should not take any[0m
[30;1m441 | [0m[35m            required parameters nor should they be expected to return a[0m
[30;1m442 | [0m[35m            meaningful value.[0m
[30;1m443 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m60 | [0m[35m        if sleep_time > 0:[0m

[30;1m561 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m562 | [0m[35mThe `run_huey` management command was simplified as we are dropping support for[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m870[0m[34m of [0m[33m902[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000600[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Windows[0m
  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/huey-2.5.3/CHANGELOG.md[0m
   Pattern: [32m\s(advpack\.dll|appvlp|at|atbroker|bash|bginfo|bitsadmin|cdb|certutil|cl_invocation\.ps1|cl_mutexverifiers\.ps1|cmd|cmdkey|cmstp|comsvcs\.dll|control|csc|cscript|csi|devtoolslauncher|dfsvc|diskshadow|dnscmd|dnx|dotnet|dxcap|esentutl|eventvwr|excel|expand|extexport|extrac32|findstr|forfiles|ftp|gfxdownloadwrapper|gpscript|hh|ie4uinit|ieadvpack\.dll|ieaframe\.dll|ic|infdefaultinstall|installutil|jsc|makecab|manage-bde\.wsf|mavinject|mftrace|microsoft\.workflow\.compiler|mmc|msbuild|msconfig|msdeploy|msdt|mshta|mshtml\.dll|msc|msxsl|netsh|odbcconf|pcalua|pcwrun|pcwutl\.dll|pester\.bat|powerpnt|presentationhost|pubprn\.vbs|rcsi|reg|regasm|regedit|register-cimprovider|regsvcs|regsvr32|rpcping|rundll32|runonce|runscripthelper|sc|schtasks|scriptrunner|setupapi\.dll|shdocvw\.dll|shell32\.dll|slmgr\.vbs|sqldumper|sqlps|sqltoolsps|squirrel|syncappvpublishingserver|syncappvpublishingserver\.vbs|syssetup\.dll|te|tracker|tttracer|update|url\.dll|verclsid|vsjitdebugger|wab|winrm\.vbs|winword|wmic|wscript|wsl|wsreset|xwizard|zipfldr\.dll)\s[0m
[30;1m525 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m526 | [0m[35mAdded better signal handling in order to support graceful shutdown. Graceful[0m
[30;1m527 | [0m[35mshutdown involves letting workers finish executing any tasks they may be[0m
[30;1m528 | [0m[35mprocessing at the time the shutdown signal is received. The default behavior is[0m
[30;1m529 | [0m[35mto interrupt the workers mid-task. Huey uses `SIGTERM` to shutdown the[0m
[30;1m530 | [0m[35mconsumer immediately, and `SIGINT` to gracefully shutdown.[0m
[30;1m531 | [0m[35m[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m880[0m[34m of [0m[33m902[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000610[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Linux[0m
  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/huey-2.5.3/CHANGELOG.md[0m
   Pattern: [32m\s(apt|apt\-get|aria2c|arp|ash|awk|base64|bash|bpftrace|busybox|cat|chmod|chown|cp|cpan|cpulimit|crontab|csh|curl|cut|dash|dd|diff|dmesg|dmsetup|dnf|docker|dpkg|easy_install|ed|emacs|env|expand|expect|facter|find|finger|flock|fmt|ftp|gawk|gdb|gimp|git|grep|head|iftop|ionice|ip|irb|jjs|journalctl|jrunscript|ksh|ld\.so|ldconfig|logsave|ltrace|lua|mail|mawk|mount|mtr|mv|mysql|nano|nawk|nc|nice|nl|nmap|node|od|openssl|perl|pg|php|pic|pico|pip|puppet|readelf|red|rlogin|rlwrap|rpm|rpmquery|rsync|ruby|run\-mailcap|run\-parts|rvim|scp|screen|script|sed|service|setarch|sftp|shuf|smbclient|socat|sort|sqlite3|ssh|start\-stop\-daemon|stdbuf|strace|systemctl|tail|tar|taskset|tclsh|tcpdump|tee|telnet|tftp|time|timeout|tmux|top|ul|unexpand|uniq|unshare|vi|vim|watch|wget|whois|wish|xargs|xxd|yum|zsh|zypper)\s[0m
[30;1m525 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m526 | [0m[35mAdded better signal handling in order to support graceful shutdown. Graceful[0m
[30;1m527 | [0m[35mshutdown involves letting workers finish executing any tasks they may be[0m
[30;1m528 | [0m[35mprocessing at the time the shutdown signal is received. The default behavior is[0m
[30;1m529 | [0m[35mto interrupt the workers mid-task. Huey uses `SIGTERM` to shutdown the[0m
[30;1m530 | [0m[35mconsumer immediately, and `SIGINT` to gracefully shutdown.[0m
[30;1m531 | [0m[35m[0m
